Note that the Appwrite Web SDK (`appwrite` package) does **not** support creating buckets — that's a server-side operation requiring an API key. Bucket creation must be done either via the Appwrite Console, the CLI, or the server SDK (`node-appwrite`). I'll show you both: a server-side script to create the bucket, and the client-side Web SDK code to upload and preview the file.

## 1. Create the Bucket (Server-side — required)

```typescript
// create-bucket.ts — run once with Node.js
import { Client, Storage, Permission, Role, ID } from 'node-appwrite';

const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject(process.env.APPWRITE_PROJECT_ID!)
    .setKey(process.env.APPWRITE_API_KEY!);

const storage = new Storage(client);

const bucket = await storage.createBucket({
    bucketId: ID.unique(),
    name: 'User Images',
    permissions: [
        Permission.read(Role.any()),            // anyone can read files
        Permission.create(Role.users()),        // any logged-in user can upload
        Permission.update(Role.users()),        // any logged-in user can update their files
        Permission.delete(Role.users()),        // any logged-in user can delete their files
    ],
    fileSecurity: true,                         // also enforce file-level permissions
    enabled: true,
    maximumFileSize: 10_000_000,                // 10 MB
    allowedFileExtensions: ['jpg', 'jpeg', 'png', 'webp', 'gif'],
    compression: 'gzip',
    encryption: true,
    antivirus: true,
});

console.log('Bucket created:', bucket.$id);
```

## 2. Upload a File and Get a Preview URL (Web SDK — client-side)

```typescript
// upload.ts — runs in the browser
import { Client, Storage, Permission, Role, ID } from 'appwrite';

const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject('[PROJECT_ID]');

const storage = new Storage(client);

const BUCKET_ID = '[BUCKET_ID]'; // from step 1

async function uploadAndPreview() {
    const fileInput = document.getElementById('file-input') as HTMLInputElement;
    const selectedFile = fileInput.files![0];

    // Upload with file-level permissions
    const uploaded = await storage.createFile({
        bucketId: BUCKET_ID,
        fileId: ID.unique(),
        file: selectedFile,
        permissions: [
            Permission.read(Role.any()),                 // public preview
            Permission.update(Role.user('[USER_ID]')),   // only the owner can update
            Permission.delete(Role.user('[USER_ID]')),   // only the owner can delete
        ],
    });

    console.log('Uploaded file ID:', uploaded.$id);

    // Get a preview URL (transformed image)
    const previewUrl = storage.getFilePreview({
        bucketId: BUCKET_ID,
        fileId: uploaded.$id,
        width: 400,
        height: 400,
        gravity: 'center',
        quality: 90,
        output: 'webp',
    });

    // Render it
    const img = document.createElement('img');
    img.src = previewUrl.toString();
    document.body.appendChild(img);

    return previewUrl.toString();
}

document.getElementById('upload-btn')?.addEventListener('click', uploadAndPreview);
```

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<input type="file" id="file-input" accept="image/*" />
<button id="upload-btn">Upload</button>
```

### Key things to know

- **Bucket creation requires a server SDK + API key** — it cannot be done from the browser. Alternatively, create the bucket once via the Appwrite Console or CLI.
- **Two layers of permissions:**
  - **Bucket-level** (set in step 1) — default rules for all files
  - **File-level** (set in step 2, requires `fileSecurity: true` on the bucket) — per-file overrides
- **`getFilePreview()`** only works on image files (jpg, png, webp, gif, etc.) and returns a transformed URL. For non-image files use `getFileView()` (inline) or `getFileDownload()` (attachment).
- **`Role.any()` on read** makes the file publicly accessible — anyone with the URL can view it. Use `Role.user('[USER_ID]')` or `Role.users()` if you need it private.

